			<div id = "comment-2436" class = "comment">
				<p>The post to which you refer is about best practices: it's great advice, but not a requirement. It also applies specifically to **troubleshooting** posts not to all posts. If someone is trying to fix something broken, OS version information can be very helpful. There are many other categories posts that don't need OS version information, though, and we don't usually add a lot of **requirements** here. You seem to propose we make it mandatory (how? delete all posts that don't include OS info?), and that's not how we generally roll here. Good idea often, helpful, but not a general requirement.</p>
